-- Morgan Stanley hires senior Barclays executive - NYT
-- By Amrutha Gayathri in Bangalore
-- Tue May 13, 2014 05:53PM EDT
-- None



May 13 (Reuters) - Morgan Stanley <MS.N> has hired a senior Barclays Plc <BARC.L> executive, the New York Times reported, citing an internal memo from the U.S. bank.

Morgan Stanley has hired Brad Whitman as a vice chairman in its financial institutions group, the report said on Tuesday. (http://r.reuters.com/gun39v) Whitman, who served as the head of mergers for financial institutions at Barclays, joins the recent drain of bankers from the British company as it moves to scale down its investment banking operation.